1
00:00:10,010 --> 00:00:13,379
[ MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS ]

2
00:01:26,119 --> 00:01:28,754
[ HAIR DRYER WHIRRING ]

3
00:02:36,322 --> 00:02:39,224
-MMM, WHAT ARE YOU DOING, BABE?

4
00:02:39,226 --> 00:02:41,226
-GOING TO WORK.

5
00:02:41,228 --> 00:02:42,594
IT'S RAININ'.

6
00:02:42,596 --> 00:02:45,664
-NO. I'LL DRIVE YA.

7
00:02:45,666 --> 00:02:48,433
I GOT TO CASH MY CHECK.

8
00:02:48,435 --> 00:02:50,936
-WELL, HURRY UP.

9
00:02:50,938 --> 00:02:52,404
I'M GONNA BE LATE.

10
00:02:52,406 --> 00:02:54,540
[ KEYS JINGLE ]

11
00:02:54,542 --> 00:02:55,874
-WELL, GOOD MORNING TO <i>YOU,</i> TOO.

12
00:02:55,876 --> 00:02:59,778
HM, LOOK AT YOU.

13
00:02:59,780 --> 00:03:01,180
-WHAT?

14
00:03:01,182 --> 00:03:02,381
-YOU LOOK GREAT.

15
00:03:02,383 --> 00:03:04,516
I LOVE THAT COLOR ON YOU.

16
00:03:04,518 --> 00:03:06,351
-[ LAUGHS ]

17
00:03:06,353 --> 00:03:07,619
LET'S GO.

18
00:03:07,621 --> 00:03:09,855
-ALL RIGHT.
HOLD YOUR HORSES.

19
00:03:09,857 --> 00:03:12,224
[ SIGHS ]

20
00:03:12,226 --> 00:03:14,860
[ THUNDER RUMBLES ]

21
00:03:26,806 --> 00:03:28,340
SO, I'LL TELL YOU
WHAT I'M GONNA DO.

22
00:03:28,342 --> 00:03:29,641
-YEAH?
-WHERE'S THAT LIST?

23
00:03:29,643 --> 00:03:31,343
-WATCH OUT.
THAT PERSON --

24
00:03:31,345 --> 00:03:32,744
-AHH. I HAD A LIST WITH ME.

25
00:03:32,746 --> 00:03:34,313
IT'S GOOD TO MAKE LISTS
OF STUFF. IT'S GOOD.

26
00:03:34,315 --> 00:03:36,815
I ALWAYS MAKE A LIST
SO I DON'T FORGET.

27
00:03:36,817 --> 00:03:37,950
-THAT'S WHAT I KEEP TELLING YOU.

28
00:03:37,952 --> 00:03:39,451
-ANYWAY.

29
00:03:39,453 --> 00:03:41,520
ALL RIGHT.
SO, I'M GONNA CASH MY CHECK,

30
00:03:41,522 --> 00:03:43,288
AND, UH, THEN WE'LL DO
A LITTLE SHOPPING,

31
00:03:43,290 --> 00:03:46,858
GET SOME FOOD AND SOME BEER.

32
00:03:46,860 --> 00:03:50,462
I GOT TO FIX THAT HAM RADIO
FOR THAT LADY.

33
00:03:50,464 --> 00:03:53,298
THAT'S GONNA PROBABLY BRING IN
A COUPLE BUCKS.

34
00:03:53,300 --> 00:03:55,934
IF I CAN FIGURE OUT THE WHOLE,
YOU KNOW...

35
00:03:55,936 --> 00:03:57,736
SHIT.
[ ENGINE SLOWS ]

36
00:03:57,738 --> 00:04:00,706
-WHAT? WHAT?

37
00:04:00,708 --> 00:04:03,875
-WE'RE LOW ON GAS.
<i>REAL</i> LOW.

38
00:04:03,877 --> 00:04:07,512
-FUCK IT.

39
00:04:07,514 --> 00:04:08,914
SAY A PRAYER.

40
00:04:08,916 --> 00:04:11,617
-[ SIGHS ]

41
00:04:11,619 --> 00:04:13,785
[ ENGINE SPUTTERING,
RADIO CHATTER ]

42
00:04:13,787 --> 00:04:15,287
-DAMN IT.

43
00:04:15,289 --> 00:04:16,888
-WHAT?

44
00:04:16,890 --> 00:04:18,290
-[ SLAMS STEERING WHEEL ]

45
00:04:18,292 --> 00:04:19,558
-FOR REAL?

46
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,967
-SORRY, BABE.

47
00:04:28,969 --> 00:04:31,703
-GOD DAMN IT.

48
00:04:33,740 --> 00:04:34,973
OKAY.

49
00:04:34,975 --> 00:04:36,642
WISH ME LUCK.

50
00:04:36,644 --> 00:04:38,877
-YEAH.
ALL RIGHT. I'LL SEE YOU.

51
00:04:38,879 --> 00:04:40,279
-WHAT ARE <i>YOU</i> GONNA DO?

52
00:04:40,281 --> 00:04:41,780
-I'M JUST GONNA WAIT IT OUT.

53
00:04:41,782 --> 00:04:43,015
-YOU SURE?
-YEAH.

54
00:04:43,017 --> 00:04:46,285
YEAH, DON'T WORRY ABOUT ME.
GO AHEAD.

55
00:04:46,287 --> 00:04:47,486
-[ SIGHS ]

56
00:04:47,488 --> 00:04:48,720
-YOU GOT IT. IT'S OKAY.

57
00:04:48,722 --> 00:04:50,389
[ RADIO SWITCHES OFF ]

58
00:04:50,391 --> 00:04:51,657
-OKAY.

59
00:04:54,427 --> 00:04:56,795
I'LL SEE YOU LATER.

60
00:04:59,032 --> 00:05:01,900
OH, COME ON, RICH.

61
00:05:01,902 --> 00:05:03,669
IT'S NOT YOUR FAULT.

62
00:05:03,671 --> 00:05:05,937
I'M THE ONE WHO DROVE IT LAST.

63
00:05:05,939 --> 00:05:07,539
-YEAH, BUT STILL.

64
00:05:07,541 --> 00:05:10,976
MAN.

65
00:05:10,978 --> 00:05:13,478
-OKAY. HERE I GO.

66
00:05:25,625 --> 00:05:27,959
[ THUNDER RUMBLES ]

67
00:05:33,533 --> 00:05:36,601
[ SIREN WAILING ]

68
00:05:47,380 --> 00:05:50,415
[ HORN BLARES ]

69
00:06:12,739 --> 00:06:14,673
SORRY I'M LATE.

70
00:06:14,675 --> 00:06:16,975
-HMM.

71
00:06:16,977 --> 00:06:20,779
I PERSONALLY DON'T GIVE A SHIT,
BUT EDWIN'S PISSED OFF.

72
00:06:20,781 --> 00:06:22,714
AY, MAMITA.

73
00:06:22,716 --> 00:06:25,050
YOUR HAIR'S A MESS.

74
00:06:25,052 --> 00:06:27,052
WHY DON'T YOU GO FIX IT
BEFORE I LEAVE, HUH?

75
00:06:27,054 --> 00:06:28,487
-[ SIGHS ] I WILL.

76
00:06:28,489 --> 00:06:32,624
-[ SPEAKING SPANISH ]

77
00:06:32,626 --> 00:06:34,459
-WHAT?

78
00:06:34,461 --> 00:06:37,462
-COQUITO.

79
00:06:37,464 --> 00:06:39,064
CHRISTMAS <i>IS</i> COMING.

80
00:06:39,066 --> 00:06:40,932
-YEAH, IN TWO MONTHS.

81
00:06:40,934 --> 00:06:42,968
DID YOUR CALENDAR BREAK?

82
00:06:42,970 --> 00:06:44,169
OH, I FORGOT.

83
00:06:44,171 --> 00:06:45,604
YOU DON'T KNOW HOW TO READ.

84
00:06:45,606 --> 00:06:47,406
-OH. HA HA HA.

85
00:06:47,408 --> 00:06:49,107
YOU WANT SOME OR NOT, SMART ASS?

86
00:06:49,109 --> 00:06:50,809
-SURE.

87
00:06:50,811 --> 00:06:52,444
[ SPEAKS SPANISH ]

88
00:06:52,446 --> 00:06:53,779
-[ REPEATS PHRASE IN SPANISH,
CHUCKLES ]

89
00:06:53,781 --> 00:06:55,480
YOU SOUND LIKE A MEXICAN.

90
00:06:55,482 --> 00:06:59,184
NOW, THAT'S SOME STRAIGHT UP
PUERTO RICAN COQUITO,

91
00:06:59,186 --> 00:07:01,987
NOT SOME MEXICAN BULLSHIT.

92
00:07:01,989 --> 00:07:05,824
-OH, GOOD MORNING.
LOOK WHO DECIDED TO JOIN US.

93
00:07:05,826 --> 00:07:07,993
-OH, SHIT.
-[ CHUCKLES LIGHTLY ]

94
00:07:07,995 --> 00:07:10,962
YOU'D BETTER CALL MANAGEMENT
TO COMPLAIN.

95
00:07:10,964 --> 00:07:13,064
OH, WAIT. HE <i>IS</i> MANAGEMENT.

96
00:07:13,066 --> 00:07:14,666
-[ CHUCKLES ]

97
00:07:14,668 --> 00:07:16,134
-BEST WATCH YOUR MOUTH, WINTERS.

98
00:07:16,136 --> 00:07:19,905
COULD HAVE YOU FIRED
FOR BEING LATE AGAIN.

99
00:07:19,907 --> 00:07:22,974
YOU KNOW, I GIVE YOU
THE BEST SHIFT OF THE DAY,

100
00:07:22,976 --> 00:07:24,976
AND YOU STILL CAN'T BE ON TIME.

101
00:07:24,978 --> 00:07:26,178
WHY IS THAT?

102
00:07:26,180 --> 00:07:27,712
-I'M SORRY.
I'M REALLY SORRY.

103
00:07:27,714 --> 00:07:30,115
IT WON'T HAPPEN AGAIN.

104
00:07:30,117 --> 00:07:33,084
-WELL, YOU'RE WORKING
A DOUBLE HERE.

105
00:07:33,086 --> 00:07:34,853
-I KNOW. I KNOW.

106
00:07:34,855 --> 00:07:36,655
-WHAT ELSE YOU KNOW?

107
00:07:36,657 --> 00:07:39,157
YOU KNOW YOU'RE NOT SUPPOSED
TO BE SMOKING THAT CIGARETTE

108
00:07:39,159 --> 00:07:41,193
BEHIND THE COUNTER,
SO PUT IT OUT.

109
00:07:41,195 --> 00:07:42,894
-YES, SIR.

110
00:07:42,896 --> 00:07:46,865
-AND YOU OTHER ONE,
YOU FIXING TO PAY FOR THOSE?

111
00:07:46,867 --> 00:07:48,133
-HONEY, TRUST ME.

112
00:07:48,135 --> 00:07:49,935
IF I WANTED TO STEAL SOMETHING
FROM YOU,

113
00:07:49,937 --> 00:07:52,037
IT WOULDN'T BE NO LITTLE SHIT
LIKE THIS.

114
00:07:52,039 --> 00:07:53,472
-HOW MANY CANS YOU TOOK?

115
00:07:55,608 --> 00:07:57,476
HUH?

116
00:07:57,478 --> 00:08:00,212
-THANKS.

117
00:08:00,214 --> 00:08:02,080
-YOUR PANTS ARE WET.
-YEP.

118
00:08:02,082 --> 00:08:06,151
-IT'S NOT 'CAUSE OF ME, IS IT?
[ CHUCKLES ]

119
00:08:06,153 --> 00:08:08,820
-[ SIGHS ]

120
00:08:08,822 --> 00:08:10,655
HA HA.

121
00:08:32,178 --> 00:08:34,679
[ SQUAWKING ]

122
00:09:10,249 --> 00:09:13,552
[ HORN BEEPS ]

123
00:09:18,124 --> 00:09:20,825
-ANYTHING THAT SAYS
"SWABIAN FARMS,"

124
00:09:20,827 --> 00:09:22,694
PULL IT ALL AND CHUCK IT.

125
00:09:25,331 --> 00:09:27,799
-SO, THAT COLLEGE PROGRAM,

126
00:09:27,801 --> 00:09:30,201
DOES THE COMPANY PAY FOR IT
BEFORE OR AFTER YOU SIGN UP?

127
00:09:30,203 --> 00:09:31,970
-WELL, FIRST OFF,

128
00:09:31,972 --> 00:09:35,674
YOU GOT TO BE WORKING HERE
A FULL 12 MONTHS TO QUALIFY.

129
00:09:35,676 --> 00:09:36,975
I TOLD YOU THAT BEFORE.

130
00:09:36,977 --> 00:09:39,144
SECONDLY, YOU DON'T SIGN UP.
YOU APPLY.

131
00:09:39,146 --> 00:09:40,679
-JUST TELL ME.

132
00:09:40,681 --> 00:09:42,347
DO THEY PAY BEFORE
OR AFTER YOU SIGN UP?

133
00:09:42,349 --> 00:09:44,082
-I DON'T KNOW.

134
00:09:44,084 --> 00:09:46,217
MAYBE YOU SHOULD CALL THE LADY
IN CHARGE AND ASK HER.

135
00:09:46,219 --> 00:09:49,654
BETTER YET, MAYBE YOU CAN
LOOK IT UP ONLINE.

136
00:09:49,656 --> 00:09:52,257
-LADY? WHAT'S HER NAME?

137
00:09:56,262 --> 00:09:58,096
[ SIGHS ]

138
00:10:03,102 --> 00:10:04,636
WHERE DO YOU WANT IT?

139
00:10:04,638 --> 00:10:06,171
-YOU'RE NOT DONE, ARE YOU?

140
00:10:06,173 --> 00:10:09,107
YOU DIDN'T GET THAT
PEANUT BUTTER OVER THERE.

141
00:10:09,109 --> 00:10:11,109
SAYS "SWABIAN FARMS" ON IT,
DON'T IT?

142
00:10:11,111 --> 00:10:13,878
DIDN'T I SAY ANYTHING THAT SAID
"SWABIAN FARMS" ON IT?

143
00:10:13,880 --> 00:10:15,614
GEEZ.

144
00:10:21,621 --> 00:10:23,989
-YOU THROWING ALL OF IT AWAY?

145
00:10:23,991 --> 00:10:25,690
-SURE AM.

146
00:10:25,692 --> 00:10:28,126
-CAN I TAKE SOME HOME?

147
00:10:28,128 --> 00:10:32,964
[  <i>HIP-HOP MUSIC PLAYING,</i>
<i>BASS THUMPING</i> ]

148
00:10:32,966 --> 00:10:34,733
-♪ <i>TELL 'EM 'BOUT IT</i> ♪

149
00:10:34,735 --> 00:10:36,868
♪ <i>THESE SWEET BUNCH</i>
<i>OF B-B-BROWNIES</i> ♪

150
00:10:36,870 --> 00:10:38,003
-LOOK AT THAT.

151
00:10:38,005 --> 00:10:41,139
LOOK AT THAT.

152
00:10:41,141 --> 00:10:43,274
[ SCOFFS ]

153
00:10:43,276 --> 00:10:45,744
THAT AIN'T NO WAY
TO LIVE RIGHT THERE.

154
00:10:45,746 --> 00:10:47,012
-YEAH.

155
00:10:47,014 --> 00:10:48,713
HEY, DAD.

156
00:10:48,715 --> 00:10:51,249
DO YOU THINK WHEN WE GET HOME,
WE CAN GO SHOOTING?

157
00:10:51,251 --> 00:10:53,718
-YOU CAN GO SHOOTING
WITH YOUR UNCLE JACK.

158
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:55,920
I GOT SOME BUSINESS
TO TAKE CARE OF FIRST.

159
00:10:55,922 --> 00:10:57,689
-OKAY.

160
00:10:57,691 --> 00:11:01,726
-[ SIGHS ]
I HATE THAT FUCKING GIMP.

161
00:11:01,728 --> 00:11:04,129
-[ CHUCKLES ]

162
00:11:04,131 --> 00:11:07,432
FUCKING GIMP.

163
00:11:07,434 --> 00:11:09,267
-DAMN STRAIGHT.

164
00:11:09,269 --> 00:11:12,971
-♪ <i>I PAINT A FUCKING PICTURE</i> ♪

165
00:11:12,973 --> 00:11:16,841
[ MACHINERY DRILLING ]

166
00:11:28,287 --> 00:11:32,223
-NOT SUCH A GOOD DAY
FOR ROLLING AROUND, IS IT?

167
00:11:32,225 --> 00:11:34,192
-TELL ME ABOUT IT.

168
00:11:34,194 --> 00:11:37,062
[ Panting ] I RAN OUT OF GAS

169
00:11:37,064 --> 00:11:40,265
DRIVING MELISSA TO WORK
THIS MORNING.

170
00:11:40,267 --> 00:11:41,966
-SORRY TO HEAR IT.

171
00:11:41,968 --> 00:11:43,768
-NO, MAN. <i>I'M</i> SORRY.

172
00:11:43,770 --> 00:11:46,204
I'M SORRY FOR <i>HER.</i>

173
00:11:46,206 --> 00:11:47,706
-SHE'S TOUGH.

174
00:11:47,708 --> 00:11:49,941
-YOU GOT THAT RIGHT.

175
00:11:49,943 --> 00:11:52,077
SHE DON'T EVEN CARE.

176
00:11:52,079 --> 00:11:54,979
I'M THE ONE WHO FEELS LIKE
A PIECE OF SHIT ABOUT IT.

177
00:11:54,981 --> 00:11:56,448
-YOU WANT TO EAT SOMETHING?

178
00:11:56,450 --> 00:11:58,416
-SURE.

179
00:11:58,418 --> 00:12:01,419
AND I GOT MY CHECK, TOO.

180
00:12:01,421 --> 00:12:03,822
YOU CASH THAT FOR ME?

181
00:12:03,824 --> 00:12:05,924
-YEAH.

182
00:12:05,926 --> 00:12:08,159
-THANKS.
-BURGER AND GRITS?

183
00:12:08,161 --> 00:12:10,328
-YEAH. AND, UH, GET ME A BEER
WITH THAT, TOO.

184
00:12:10,330 --> 00:12:12,363
I AIN'T STAYING.

185
00:12:12,365 --> 00:12:13,832
[ SIGHS ]

186
00:12:13,834 --> 00:12:16,968
-$1.50, PLEASE.
THANK YOU.

187
00:12:16,970 --> 00:12:20,271
[ DOOR CHIMES ]
HAVE A NICE DAY.

188
00:12:24,376 --> 00:12:26,745
-I SAW YOUR BOYFRIEND
THIS MORNING

189
00:12:26,747 --> 00:12:29,781
ROLLING DOWN THE HIGHWAY...

190
00:12:29,783 --> 00:12:31,750
LIKE A BUM.

191
00:12:35,888 --> 00:12:38,857
-I'M CALLING THE COPS.
-IT'S LEGAL.

192
00:12:38,859 --> 00:12:40,358
THERE AIN'T NOTHING THEY CAN DO.

193
00:12:40,360 --> 00:12:43,862
SO, I'VE BEEN SEEING
KRYSTAL LATELY.

194
00:12:43,864 --> 00:12:46,865
-YEAH?
-MM-HMM. SHE'S HOT.

195
00:12:46,867 --> 00:12:50,502
MAKES ME DINNER EVERY NIGHT,
SUCKS MY DICK <i>REAL</i> GOOD.

196
00:12:50,504 --> 00:12:52,370
-CAN I HELP YOU, SIR?

197
00:12:52,372 --> 00:12:57,041
-YOU'RE GOING OUT WITH A GIMP
'CAUSE YOU FUCKED UP...AGAIN.

198
00:12:57,043 --> 00:12:58,343
-I GOT A WEAPON DOWN HERE.

199
00:12:58,345 --> 00:12:59,544
-YEAH, WHAT DO YOU GOT?

200
00:12:59,546 --> 00:13:01,146
YOU GOT AN A.K., UZI?

201
00:13:01,148 --> 00:13:04,215
[ CASH REGISTER BEEPS, WHIRS ]

202
00:13:04,217 --> 00:13:06,217
-THAT'S $3.62.

203
00:13:06,219 --> 00:13:09,387
HAVE A NICE DAY.

204
00:13:09,389 --> 00:13:12,123
[ DOOR CHIMES ]

205
00:13:12,125 --> 00:13:13,358
-I MISS YOU.

206
00:13:13,360 --> 00:13:15,994
-DON'T.

207
00:13:15,996 --> 00:13:17,896
JUST THE WATER?

208
00:13:17,898 --> 00:13:20,331
-YEAH.
[ CASH REGISTER BEEPS ]

209
00:13:20,333 --> 00:13:23,301
[ COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYING,
MACHINERY DRILLING ]

210
00:13:23,303 --> 00:13:25,904
-WHAT ARE THEY BUILDING
OVER THERE, MICK?

211
00:13:25,906 --> 00:13:28,139
-PROBABLY ANOTHER
FUCKING STRIP MALL.

212
00:13:28,141 --> 00:13:32,076
-YEAH, RIGHT?
JUST WHAT WE NEED.

213
00:13:33,913 --> 00:13:36,047
-YOU MISS WORKING CONSTRUCTION?

214
00:13:36,049 --> 00:13:37,549
-HELL NO.

215
00:13:37,551 --> 00:13:40,451
BUT YOU CAN MAKE
A GOOD LIVING AT IT.

216
00:13:40,453 --> 00:13:42,387
I DID PRETTY GOOD AT IT.

217
00:13:42,389 --> 00:13:44,289
I MADE SOME GOOD MONEY.

218
00:13:44,291 --> 00:13:45,924
-[ Scoffing ] YEAH.

219
00:13:45,926 --> 00:13:48,326
WHAT HAPPENED TO THAT?

220
00:13:48,328 --> 00:13:50,228
-MAN, THAT MONEY'S HISTORY.

221
00:13:50,230 --> 00:13:51,896
"WHAT HAPPENED TO IT?"

222
00:13:51,898 --> 00:13:54,299
SHIT, MAN.
LIFE HAPPENED TO THAT.

223
00:13:54,301 --> 00:13:57,902
I GAMBLED IT, YOU KNOW.

224
00:13:57,904 --> 00:14:01,272
I HAD THIS OTHER GIRL BACK THEN,
THIS GIRL TAMMY.

225
00:14:01,274 --> 00:14:06,544
MAN, THIS CHICK
WAS A PIECE OF WORK.

226
00:14:06,546 --> 00:14:09,981
SHE WAS A BORDERLINE
PERSONALITY DISORDER.

227
00:14:09,983 --> 00:14:11,549
YOU EVER MET ONE OF THEM?

228
00:14:11,551 --> 00:14:13,885
-YOU'RE CRAZY, MAN.
-NO, MAN.

229
00:14:13,887 --> 00:14:15,520
<i>SHE</i> WAS CRAZY.

230
00:14:15,522 --> 00:14:18,122
SHE WAS BAT-SHIT CRAZY.

231
00:14:18,124 --> 00:14:21,192
[ COINS SCRAPING ]

232
00:14:21,194 --> 00:14:22,427
-HOW'S KYLE?

233
00:14:22,429 --> 00:14:24,429
-THANK YOU.

234
00:14:24,431 --> 00:14:25,864
-HE AIN'T YOURS.

235
00:14:25,866 --> 00:14:28,132
I DON'T KNOW WHAT DIFFERENCE
IT MAKES.

236
00:14:28,134 --> 00:14:29,400
-HEY, JIMMY.
HOW YOU DOING?

237
00:14:29,402 --> 00:14:30,969
-GREAT. THANK YOU.
-PACK OF SMOKES?

238
00:14:30,971 --> 00:14:32,637
-PLEASE.
HOW YOU DOING, MEL?

239
00:14:32,639 --> 00:14:34,639
-I'M ALL RIGHT.

240
00:14:34,641 --> 00:14:38,509
-I MISS YOUR ASS.

241
00:14:38,511 --> 00:14:40,511
IS IT STILL FAT?
-SHUT UP, JUSTIN.

242
00:14:40,513 --> 00:14:41,913
-WATCH IT, GUY.

243
00:14:41,915 --> 00:14:43,214
-DON'T WORRY, JIMMY.
