1028
00:58:21,232 --> 00:58:23,732
[ Fading ] YOU CAN GET
THESE PUBLICATIONS

1029
00:58:23,734 --> 00:58:25,100
EITHER FROM OUR WEBSITE...

1030
00:58:25,102 --> 00:58:28,003
[ BELL TOLLING ]

1031
00:58:40,517 --> 00:58:43,886
[ TOLLING CONTINUES ]

1032
00:58:48,057 --> 00:58:51,627
[ Distantly ] MR. BARNES?

1033
00:58:51,629 --> 00:58:53,729
[ Normal voice ] MR. BARNES?
-HUH?

1034
00:58:53,731 --> 00:58:55,931
-DO YOU HAVE
HIGH-TECH EXPERIENCE?

1035
00:58:55,933 --> 00:58:58,534
-YOU MEAN LIKE, UH, COMPUTERS?

1036
00:58:58,536 --> 00:59:00,802
-THAT'S RIGHT.
-NAH.

1037
00:59:00,804 --> 00:59:03,705
I MEAN, YEAH,
I CAN GET ON THE INTERNET,

1038
00:59:03,707 --> 00:59:06,675
YOU KNOW, BUT I CAN'T FIX THEM
OR NOTHING.

1039
00:59:06,677 --> 00:59:09,011
I MEAN, UM,
YOU KNOW WHAT I FIX?

1040
00:59:09,013 --> 00:59:11,079
I FIX, LIKE, TELEVISION SETS,

1041
00:59:11,081 --> 00:59:14,016
ELECTRONICS, STUFF LIKE THAT,
YOU KNOW?

1042
00:59:14,018 --> 00:59:15,918
MID-TECH, I CALL IT.

1043
00:59:15,920 --> 00:59:17,252
-ALL RIGHT. WELL,

1044
00:59:17,254 --> 00:59:19,555
I'M SURE THERE ARE
SOME CLASSES IN THERE

1045
00:59:19,557 --> 00:59:21,156
FOR YOU TO UPDATE YOUR SKILLS.

1046
00:59:21,158 --> 00:59:22,991
YOU LOOK IN THERE.

1047
00:59:22,993 --> 00:59:24,560
-[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

1048
00:59:24,562 --> 00:59:26,061
-AND I'LL SEE YOU NEXT MONTH.

1049
00:59:26,063 --> 00:59:27,262
OKAY?

1050
00:59:27,264 --> 00:59:29,865
-THANKS.

1051
00:59:33,770 --> 00:59:35,904
-JUST SEEMED LIKE
A LOT OF BLOOD.

1052
00:59:35,906 --> 00:59:39,174
-WELL, I'VE HAD PATIENTS BLEED
THEIR WHOLE PREGNANCY LONG

1053
00:59:39,176 --> 00:59:40,776
AND EVERYTHING WAS FINE.

1054
00:59:40,778 --> 00:59:43,145
-[ SIGHS ]
I HOPE THAT'S NOT ME.

1055
00:59:43,147 --> 00:59:44,880
-IT'S VERY RARE.

1056
00:59:44,882 --> 00:59:48,116
IT USUALLY RESOLVES ITSELF
AFTER THE FIRST TRIMESTER.

1057
00:59:48,118 --> 00:59:51,320
YOU SAID YOU HAD A SONOGRAM.
IS THAT CORRECT?

1058
00:59:51,322 --> 00:59:52,788
-OH, YES, MA'AM.

1059
00:59:54,724 --> 00:59:56,992
SEE?

1060
00:59:56,994 --> 00:59:58,894
IT WAS KICKING ITS LITTLE LEGS

1061
00:59:58,896 --> 01:00:01,797
AND PUNCHING ITS LITTLE FISTS
THE WHOLE TIME.

1062
01:00:01,799 --> 01:00:03,632
I COULDN'T HARDLY BELIEVE IT.

1063
01:00:03,634 --> 01:00:05,100
-THAT'S GOOD.

1064
01:00:07,103 --> 01:00:08,971
ALL RIGHT.

1065
01:00:08,973 --> 01:00:10,172
EXCELLENT.

1066
01:00:10,174 --> 01:00:11,907
-THANKS.

1067
01:00:11,909 --> 01:00:14,142
-WOULD YOU LIKE
TO KEEP A JOURNAL?

1068
01:00:14,144 --> 01:00:16,678
I SOMETIMES ASK MY PATIENTS
TO DO THAT.

1069
01:00:16,680 --> 01:00:18,981
IN FACT, I HAD ONE PATIENT
THAT TOLD ME

1070
01:00:18,983 --> 01:00:21,383
SHE USED IT TO WRITE LETTERS
TO HER BABY.

1071
01:00:21,385 --> 01:00:24,119
-OH, OKAY. THANKS.

1072
01:00:26,389 --> 01:00:28,790
SO...

1073
01:00:28,792 --> 01:00:31,793
SHOULD I BRING THIS BACK
NEXT TIME I'M HERE?

1074
01:00:31,795 --> 01:00:34,363
-OH, NO.
IT'S NOT FOR ME, IT'S FOR YOU.

1075
01:00:34,365 --> 01:00:36,398
-OH, OKAY.
I-I'M SORRY.

1076
01:00:36,400 --> 01:00:40,869
I THOUGHT IT WAS, LIKE, SOME
KIND OF HOMEWORK OR SOMETHING.

1077
01:00:40,871 --> 01:00:42,638
-[ CHUCKLES ]

1078
01:00:42,640 --> 01:00:45,273
THE ONLY HOMEWORK YOU HAVE
IS TO TAKE CARE OF YOURSELF.

1079
01:00:45,275 --> 01:00:46,775
EAT HEALTHY AND NO SMOKING.

1080
01:00:46,777 --> 01:00:49,411
-OH, YES, MA'AM.

1081
01:00:49,413 --> 01:00:51,213
[ GULPS ]

1082
01:00:53,950 --> 01:00:55,851
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

1083
01:00:55,853 --> 01:00:57,285
<i>-THE SCRATCH-OFF GAME</i>

1084
01:00:57,287 --> 01:00:59,655
<i>WITH THE HIGHEST PRIZE</i>
<i>PAYOFF PERCENTAGE EVER!</i>

1085
01:00:59,657 --> 01:01:02,057
<i>25 PEOPLE WILL BECOME</i>
<i>INSTANT MILLIONAIRES...</i>

1086
01:01:02,059 --> 01:01:04,292
-HEY, IS THIS YOURS?

1087
01:01:04,294 --> 01:01:07,829
-NO, IT'S OKAY.
YOU CAN HAVE IT.

1088
01:01:07,831 --> 01:01:10,032
<i>-SO KEEP</i>
<i>THE WINNING STREAK ALIVE,</i>

1089
01:01:10,034 --> 01:01:14,136
<i>AND PLAY THE 25th ANNIVERSARY</i>
<i>MILLIONAIRE SCRATCH-OFF GAME...</i>

1090
01:01:14,138 --> 01:01:17,072
[ CRICKETS CHIRPING,
OWL HOOTING ]

1091
01:01:32,355 --> 01:01:34,990
-STOP IT, RICH.

1092
01:01:34,992 --> 01:01:37,959
-EXCUSE ME?

1093
01:01:42,398 --> 01:01:44,366
-LEAVE ME ALONE!

1094
01:01:44,368 --> 01:01:47,235
GOD DAMN IT. JESUS.

1095
01:01:47,237 --> 01:01:49,371
-SO, WHY DON'T YOU TAKE A NAP?

1096
01:01:49,373 --> 01:01:52,307
DO YOU REALIZE THAT
YOU'RE FALLING ASLEEP?

1097
01:01:52,309 --> 01:01:53,909
-I'M NOT. I'M READING.

1098
01:01:53,911 --> 01:01:55,744
-IF YOU FALL ASLEEP AGAIN,

1099
01:01:55,746 --> 01:01:59,047
THEN I'M -- I'M GONNA INSIST
THAT YOU TAKE A NAP.

1100
01:02:00,817 --> 01:02:03,118
[ DOOR CHIMES ]

1101
01:02:03,120 --> 01:02:04,753
YOU'RE ASLEEP AGAIN.

1102
01:02:04,755 --> 01:02:06,054
HEY, HOW YOU DOING?
-ALL RIGHT.

1103
01:02:06,056 --> 01:02:08,023
LET ME KNOW
IF I CAN GET YOU ANYTHING.

1104
01:02:08,025 --> 01:02:09,357
-YEP.

1105
01:02:09,359 --> 01:02:12,194
-TAKE A NAP, BABE.
I'LL WATCH THE STORE.

1106
01:02:12,196 --> 01:02:14,162
YEAH, GO.

1107
01:02:14,164 --> 01:02:17,966
GO. SIT. TAKE A NAP.

1108
01:02:17,968 --> 01:02:19,267
I GOT IT.

1109
01:02:21,003 --> 01:02:23,739
[ REFRIGERATOR DOOR CLOSES,
GLASSES CLINK ]

1110
01:02:25,875 --> 01:02:28,343
-[ SIGHS ]

1111
01:02:35,284 --> 01:02:38,353
[ SOFT MUSIC PLAYS ]

1112
01:03:01,277 --> 01:03:04,946
[ MOTORS WHIRRING ]

1113
01:03:15,358 --> 01:03:16,992
[ DOOR CHIMES ]

1114
01:03:16,994 --> 01:03:18,360
HEY.

1115
01:03:18,362 --> 01:03:19,961
-HEY, WINTERS.

1116
01:03:19,963 --> 01:03:21,897
YOU AND ME NEED TO TALK.

1117
01:03:21,899 --> 01:03:23,532
RIGHT NOW.

1118
01:03:25,134 --> 01:03:26,868
NO, JUST ME AND HER.

1119
01:03:26,870 --> 01:03:28,336
-[ SCOFFS ]

1120
01:03:30,339 --> 01:03:33,108
SURE THING. TALK.

1121
01:03:33,110 --> 01:03:35,110
-WELL, APPARENTLY
YOU FORGOT THE RULES.

1122
01:03:35,112 --> 01:03:37,946
VIDEO CAMERA UP THERE'S GOT
PICTURES OF YOUR BOYFRIEND HERE

1123
01:03:37,948 --> 01:03:40,515
WAITING ON CUSTOMERS WHILE
YOU'RE SLEEPING ON THE CHAIR.

1124
01:03:40,517 --> 01:03:42,450
-HEY, HEY.

1125
01:03:42,452 --> 01:03:44,452
SHE WAS TIRED, MAN.
IT'S NO BIG DEAL.

1126
01:03:44,454 --> 01:03:45,987
IT'S NOT GONNA HAPPEN AGAIN.

1127
01:03:45,989 --> 01:03:47,289
-YOU, MY FRIEND, GOT TO GO.

1128
01:03:47,291 --> 01:03:49,491
ADIOS. GOODBYE. RIGHT NOW.
-COME ON, EDWIN.

1129
01:03:49,493 --> 01:03:51,459
-HEY, IT'S NOT SAFE
FOR A WOMAN HERE

1130
01:03:51,461 --> 01:03:52,861
ALL ALONE BY HERSELF AT NIGHT.

1131
01:03:52,863 --> 01:03:54,062
-VIVIAN DID IT.

1132
01:03:54,064 --> 01:03:56,031
-WELL,
I CAN'T SPEAK FOR VIVIAN,

1133
01:03:56,033 --> 01:03:57,899
BUT IT'S NOT SAFE FOR MELISSA.

1134
01:03:57,901 --> 01:04:00,068
-ALL RIGHT, LOOK.
EITHER HE GOES, OR YOU BOTH GO.

1135
01:04:00,070 --> 01:04:01,469
WHAT'S IT GONNA BE?

1136
01:04:01,471 --> 01:04:05,273
WHAT'S IT GONNA BE?!

1137
01:04:09,412 --> 01:04:12,280
-I'LL BE OUTSIDE.

1138
01:04:15,151 --> 01:04:17,285
[ DOOR CHIMES ]

1139
01:04:20,990 --> 01:04:23,158
-YOU ARE SO FULL OF SHIT.

1140
01:04:23,160 --> 01:04:24,593
-YEAH, WELL, I DON'T KNOW WHY

1141
01:04:24,595 --> 01:04:26,561
